 you will not have to labour cleaning the door, the lock, and the knob...\r\n\r\nYou will also need a napkin or a paper towel to remove any of the excess lube that spills out of the keyway. Additionally, grab a pair of needle nose pliers. That''s because even though these methods will remove the broken key, pliers will help to get it out much quicker. As soon as the keys begin to look out of the keyway, simply pull it out with the pliers.', '5 locks that give a false sense of security', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '64-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-05-16 07:29:14', '2016-05-16 07:29:14', '', 64, 'http://192.168.9.75/2016/mechanna/wordpress/2016/05/16/64-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
